fields.name: Minimap2
fields.long_description: Minimap2 can be used to map reads against a reference genome. Several genomes are already installed in minoTour. Others (less than 100 Mb in size) can be uploaded for your own use under 'admin'.

fields.name: Assembly
fields.long_description: Using minimap and miniasm a rapid assembly of your data will be performed every n reads generated.

fields.name: Minimap2_trans
fields.long_description: You can use minimap2 to map your reads against a reference set of transcripts available on this minoTour server. Please note that all secondary mappings are suppressed. We also use the default map-ont parameter as we are mapping to a transcriptome collection, not a genome.

fields.name: ExportLive
fields.long_description:
This service allows you to export live data collected by minoTour in a json format for analysis in other packages.
When the task is complete, you will receive an email containing a link to the json file. This link will remain active for 7 days.

fields.name: ExportReads
fields.long_description: Export fastq files split by barcode (where appropriate) from a run. Files once generated will be stored on the server for one week, then deleted.

fields.name: Delete_Flowcell
fields.long_description: Delete a flowcell from the database

fields.name: UpdateFlowcellDetails
fields.long_description: Update flowcell details in the database

fields.name: CalculateSankey
fields.long_description: Calculate the sankey diagram on demand

fields.name: Other
fields.description: Extra jobtype for non specific jobs
fields.long_description: Used now to distinguish between the two minimaps, metagenomics and alignment
